cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a task and methodology for multi-hop reading comprehension across multiple documents. The paper focuses on natural language processing and machine learning techniques to enable models to combine disjoint pieces of textual evidence. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves evaluating models and proposing strategies to improve their performance, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also involves information retrieval techniques to select relevant information, which falls under the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
